President Joe Biden hosted Permanent Representatives from the UN Security Council and reaffirmed the US commitment to values-based global leadership and engagement with international institutions, particularly the United Nations. He emphasized the importance of working with global partners and multilateral institutions to address the pandemic, improve global health security, and drive an equitable and sustainable economic recovery. President Biden also announced that the US intends to formally join the United Nation's Group of Friends on Climate and Security. He discussed the need for UNSC action on regional crises in Burma, Ethiopia, Libya, Syria, and Yemen. Special Presidential Envoy on Climate John Kerry and Principal Deputy National Security Advisor Jon Finer briefed the group on US priorities regarding climate change and regional security issues.